# SSH host shortcuts — example template
#
# This file lives in the repo as a reference. It is NOT symlinked into
# ~/.ssh/config.d/ — SSH never parses it directly.
#
# To use it:
#   cp ~/projects/dotfiles/ssh_config.d/hosts.example ~/.ssh/config.d/hosts.local
#   # Edit hosts.local with real values
#   chmod 600 ~/.ssh/config.d/hosts.local
#
# Each entry creates a shortcut: `ssh proxmox` instead of
# `ssh admin@192.168.1.100 -p 22`.
#
# Tips:
#   - The 1Password agent is already configured globally (in ssh_config),
#     so you don't need IdentityFile or IdentityAgent per host.
#   - If a host is only reachable via Tailscale, use the Tailscale IP
#     or MagicDNS hostname.

# --- Proxmox hypervisor ---
# Host proxmox
# 	HostName 100.x.x.x
# 	User root
# 	Port 22

# --- TrueNAS storage ---
# Host truenas
# 	HostName 100.x.x.x
# 	User admin
# 	Port 22

# --- Generic template ---
# Host nickname
# 	HostName <ip-or-hostname>
# 	User <username>
# 	Port 22
